      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That's a good start, but it feels a bit like it's just hitting the same talking points. I want to make the essay even more powerful by addressing the counter-arguments directly. \n\nA lot of people argue that meritocracy is the most fair way to run an economy and that redistribution actually punishes hard work. How should I frame those meritocracy arguments in my essay so they don't undermine my main point? I want to show why those views are ultimately problematic or based on a flawed understanding of how society actually works.",
