      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The meritocracy argument is a myth that ignores how systemic racism and historical exclusion have artificially suppressed the potential of marginalized groups, making \"hard work\" impossible without foundational equity. By framing these views as a defense of the status quo, you can expose how the idea of a \"level playing field\" is itself a lie perpetuated by centuries of unearned privilege. Ultimately, true merit cannot exist in a system where wealth accumulation is rigged against specific races, so redistribution is not a punishment for success but a prerequisite for genuine opportunity.",
